rComments: Not accessible outside of class, doesn't answer emails - lectures about nothing. Avoid at all cost - take the class in English or with another professor if you actually want to succeed or want a professor who cares about your wellbeing and teaching you.

Gave us an assignment at the beginning of semester, which we received perfect marks - we later presented this same assignment and he gave us poor mark and could not give us any feedback on what needed to be improved. Very condescending and does not care about his students or their success.

Has no regard for his students, or their well being. Does not answer emails and claims to not receive them, but refuses to give an alternate email address when asked. Does not give constructive criticism, just belittles students. Request you come see him when submitting the assignment to ask your questions regarding the assignment.

Great teacher. His classes are heavy but the exam is pretty easy if you understand! He's pretty upfront with what will be on the exam, doesn't play any tricks. I suggest reading the book but his PowerPoints are pretty much just a summary of everything. Group oral presentation + group project. Passionate teacher, knows what he's talking about. 100%

Son cours est assez bon. La matière se digère facilement et les PowerPoints du prof sont pas mal organisés. La majorité des points consiste des notes que vous aurez dans les projets de groupe. Donc, choisissez bien vos coéquipiers!
La matière est générale, est n'est pas trop difficile à comprendre, mais il y a bcp de travaux de groupe. Si tu n'est pas avec des bons coéquipiers... bonne chance.
Pas tellement stimulant, mais sympathique, drôle par moments. La matière n'est pas tellement intéressante, et le livre est passé-date.

Overall, it was a good class. Prof gives 2 team projects with presentation, so a good portion of your grade goes towards that. The material taught in class isn't tough, so its easy to retain. He's a pretty good prof!
